Issues.Body:
The first tutorial mentioned on the docs site (https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/machine-learning/) uses ML.NET version 0.4.0, as does the example on main GitHub readme page.  These examples require the Microsoft.ML.Legacy namespace.

Snippet from example:
`var pipeline = new LearningPipeline();
pipeline.Add(new TextLoader(dataPath).CreateFrom<SentimentData>(separator: ','));
`

### System information

- **Windows Server**:
- **.NET Version - Core 2.1**: 

### Issue
I built a demo web application that runs locally but breaks on the server. I am using WordEmbeddings. The error message is:

"Error downloading resource: Error trying to create directory : Path cannot be the empty string or all whitespace.
Parameter name: path.
Please fix your filesystem permissions, or try setting the 'MICROSOFTML_RESOURCE_PATH' environment variable to a writable folder"

I am using a service account on the IIS server and the GetFilePath method is is getting an empty string for "Environment.SpecialFolder.LocalApplicationData". I have the Environment Variable set to the appropriate folder. The issue is that the GetFilePath method is not checking for the Environment variable path at the right time and throwing the error reaching before that part of the code.

            if (!Directory.Exists(appDataBaseDir))
            {
                try
                {
                   //**for service accounts, appDataBaseDir is empty and this through the error that is caught. Perhaps need to check for empty string here?** 
                    Directory.CreateDirectory(appDataBaseDir);

                    // On unix, create with 0700 perms as per XDG base dir spec
                    if (Environment.OSVersion.Platform == PlatformID.Unix)
                        chmod(appDataBaseDir, 448);
                }
                catch (Exception e)
                {
                    error = $"Error trying to create directory {appDataBaseDir}: {e.Message}.\nPlease fix your " +
                        "filesystem permissions, or try setting the " +
                        $"'{Utils.CustomSearchDirEnvVariable}' environment variable to a writable folder";
                    return filePath;
                }
            }

           
            if (!Directory.Exists(absDir))
            {
                try
                {
                    Directory.CreateDirectory(absDir);
                }
                catch (Exception e)
                {
                    error = $"Error trying to create directory {absDir}: {e.Message}.\nPlease try setting the " +
                        $"'{Utils.CustomSearchDirEnvVariable}' environment variable to a writable folder";
                }
            }
            return filePath;
        }
